article.description: — Jordan Burns and Nelly Cummings scored 16 points apiece as Colgate extended its winning streak to seven games, beating Army 84-74 on Saturday. Jack Ferguson added 15 points for the Raiders.
article.headline: Burns, Cummings carry Colgate past Army 84-74
article.linkText: Burns, Cummings carry Colgate past Army 84-74
article.story: WEST POINT, N.Y. -- — Jordan Burns and Nelly Cummings scored 16 points apiece as Colgate extended its winning streak to seven games, beating Army 84-74 on Saturday. Jack Ferguson added 15 points for the Raiders. Tucker Richardson had 12 points, 11 rebounds and six assists for Colgate (8-1, 8-1 Patriot League). Jeff Woodward scored 10 points. Lonnie Grayson had 14 points and seven rebounds for the Black Knights (9-5, 5-4). Alex King also scored 14 points. Jalen Rucker had 13 points, Nick Finke 11 and Josh Caldwell 10. The Raiders improve to 2-1 against the Black Knights on the season. The teams meet again today. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
